+     * SetStarDist last set it to). Fixed at the root by bypassing the
+     * fragile offset-based overlay entirely and writing the REAL,
+     * named `mesh.base.scale.x`/`scale.y` fields directly through a plain
+     * HSF_OBJECT*, which is immune to pointer width (and any future
+     * HSF_OBJECT layout change) instead of re-deriving another
+     * build-specific magic-number offset pair. Semantically this is
+     * unchanged from the original's own intent (a scale pulse used as a
+     * cheap "spotlight" highlight on the currently-narrated guide
+     * character), just no longer aliased onto the wrong field. */
